load models asynchronously. These threads will only be started if the
asynchronous interface is used, and if threading support is compiled
into Panda. The default is one thread, which allows models to be loaded
one at a time in a single asychronous thread. You can set this higher,
particularly if you have many CPU's available, to allow loading multiple
models simultaneously. loader-support-entry-points bool 0 Used in the Loader class. When set to true, the loader will
additionally load python packages. loader-thread-priority enum low The default thread priority to assign to the threads created for
asynchronous loading. The default is 'low'; you may also specify
'normal', 'high', or 'urgent'. lod-fade-bin-draw-order int 0 The default bin draw order to assign the fading part of a
